<br><br>{{Underline|ffffff}}<span style="color: #000000; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #ffffff; letter-spacing: 3px">'''<span style="font-size: 40px">The</span><br><span style="font-size: 65px">Surrounding Abyss</span>'''</span>{{Underline|ffffff}}<br><br><br><br><br>
[[File:Abyss.png|650px|link=]]<br><br><br><br><br>
'''The Surrounding Abyss''' is much like [[The Void]], only with a floating, barren island made of an unidentified, grey, rock-like substance. The island is tens of meters in diameter, believed to be somewhere between 20- to 60 meters. Its top surface is mostly flat and easily traversible, as well as being where all arriving wanderers first find themselves. However, every wanderer is inexplicably alone in the level, unable to see or interact with each other.

It is impossible to leave the island, as jumping or falling off of it will result in the darkness below the wanderer parting to reveal the island, and one will land on its surface. No matter how much one attempts to leave the rocky structure, it will always end with the would-be escapist landing right back where they started. Moreover, it is impossible to leave the level, rendering it an inescapable 'dead end'.

Soon after one enters the '''Surrounding Abyss''', one will begin to hear a cacophony of loud, inhuman shrieks seemingly emanating from all directions. As well as this, one will also hear these shrieks in their mind, adding to the noise and eventually causing severe migraines in those afflicted. Furthermore, the shrieks are unceasing, meaning that any wanderers in the level will inevitably succumb to insanity. However, they will not turn into a [[Phenomenon 35|Wretch]], and they will instead suffer until they die of dehydration or starvation.


{{Collapse|num=1|initial='''. . .'''|final=|body=
<div style="background: #000000; padding: 25px 25px; border: 2px solid #ffffff; border-radius: 10px; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 18px">
<span style="color: #ffffff; font-size: 32px; text-shadow: 0 0 3px #ffffff">The Truth of the Abyss</span>
{{Underline|ffffff}}


The wanderer had spent so long trapped in this hell.


The Backrooms at large was bad enough, but this accursed island in the abyss was worse. Constant, inhuman shrieking seemed to come from everywhere at once, loud and unceasing, and it not only reached the wanderer's ears but his mind as well.


It was simply too much for the human brain to handle.


Broken from this hopeless and terrifying ordeal, the wanderer screamed into the abyss: "WHY AM I HERE!? WHY IS THIS HAPPENING TO ME!?"


The shrieks suddenly faded away entirely, and while it was a relief, apprehensive dread seeped into the wanderer nonetheless.


Then, a strange and inhuman voice spoke to him from everywhere at once, but unlike the shrieks, it was not anywhere near deafening.


<span style="color: #a30808; font-size: 21px; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #e80707">"Because you didn't run fast enough."</span>


This new voice was somehow even more terrifying than the shrieks, but the wanderer managed to find his voice.


"Wh- who are you? What does that mean?"


He shouted the questions, fear tinging his voice, though the wanderer had the intuition that whatever had just spoken to him would have heard him anyway.


<span style="color: #a30808; font-size: 21px; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #e80707">"Do you not remember how you got here? Have you forgotten what you saw?"</span>


"What do you mean?"


<span style="color: #a30808; font-size: 21px; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #e80707">"This place is not a level, nor a dimension. It is in your mind."</span>


The wanderer was not sure how to process this statement; in fact, he was not even sure whether to believe it or not.


But the voice obviously had no reason to lie. And... he was now starting to remember how he had gotten here in the first place. He had been running away from something — a shadow. Then, the shadow had got him...


...and in the blink of an eye, he had arrived here.


This whole thing... it wasn't even real.


<span style="color: #a30808; font-size: 21px; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #e80707">"You see? When I attacked you, I did not kill you — I trapped your consciousness in your own mind. I created the mindscape you see before you. And you are not the only one; hundreds more are wandering hopelessly on their own little islands... slowly dying in the real world. And there is no escape."</span>
